 estate development prevails over planned growth. At the same time, Siem Reap's marginal position allows for some freedom in architectural and urban design. In the shadow of institutional control, this architectural space expresses alternative visions of the Khmer heritage and connects them with images of urban modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCities and townszCambodiazSiĕmréab. 0aCity planningzCambodiazSiĕmréab. 0aCultural propertyxProtectionzCambodiazAngkor Archaeological Park. 0aHistoric preservationzCambodiazAngkor Archaeological Park. 4aAsian Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aWorld Heritage Cambodia Architecture Tourism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060672008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060401608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2018z9783110603231oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048534050zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048534050423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048534050.jpg  a978-3-11-060401-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11